#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:5
msgid "NumPy 2.4.0 Release Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:7
msgid ""
"The NumPy 2.4.0 release continues the work to improve free threaded Python "
"support, user dtypes implementation, and annotations. There are many expired "
"deprecations and bug fixes as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:11
msgid "This release supports Python versions 3.11-3.14"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:15
msgid "Highlights"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:17
msgid ""
"Apart from annotations and ``same_value`` kwarg, the 2.4 highlights are "
"mostly of interest to downstream developers. They should help in "
"implementing new user dtypes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:21
msgid ""
"Many annotation improvements. In particular, runtime signature introspection."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:23
msgid "New ``casting`` kwarg ``'same_value'`` for casting by value."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:25
msgid ""
"New ``PyUFunc_AddLoopsFromSpec`` function that can be used to add user sort "
"loops using the ``ArrayMethod`` API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:28
msgid "New ``__numpy_dtype__`` protocol."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:31
msgid "Deprecations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:34
msgid "Setting the ``strides`` attribute is deprecated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:35
msgid ""
"Setting the strides attribute is now deprecated since mutating an array is "
"unsafe if an array is shared, especially by multiple threads.  As an "
"alternative, you can create a new view (no copy) via:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:39
msgid "``np.lib.stride_tricks.strided_window_view`` if applicable,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:40
msgid "``np.lib.stride_tricks.as_strided`` for the general case,"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:41
msgid ""
"or the ``np.ndarray`` constructor (``buffer`` is the original array) for a "
"light-weight version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:44
msgid "(`gh-28925 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28925>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:47
msgid ""
"Positional ``out`` argument to ``np.maximum``, ``np.minimum`` is deprecated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:48
msgid ""
"Passing the output array ``out`` positionally to ``numpy.maximum`` and "
"``numpy.minimum`` is deprecated. For example, ``np.maximum(a, b, c)`` will "
"emit a deprecation warning, since ``c`` is treated as the output buffer "
"rather than a third input."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:53
msgid ""
"Always pass the output with the keyword form, e.g.  ``np.maximum(a, b, "
"out=c)``. This makes intent clear and simplifies type annotations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:56
msgid "(`gh-29052 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/29052>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:59
msgid "``align=`` must be passed as boolean to ``np.dtype()``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:60
msgid ""
"When creating a new ``dtype`` a ``VisibleDeprecationWarning`` will be given "
"if ``align=`` is not a boolean.  This is mainly to prevent accidentally "
"passing a subarray align flag where it has no effect, such as ``np."
"dtype(\"f8\", 3)`` instead of ``np.dtype((\"f8\", 3))``.  We strongly "
"suggest to always pass ``align=`` as a keyword argument."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:66
msgid "(`gh-29301 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/29301>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:69
msgid "Assertion and warning control utilities are deprecated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:70
msgid ""
"``np.testing.assert_warns`` and ``np.testing.suppress_warnings`` are "
"deprecated.  Use ``warnings.catch_warnings``, ``warnings.filterwarnings``, "
"``pytest.warns``, or ``pytest.filterwarnings`` instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:74
msgid "(`gh-29550 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/29550>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:77
msgid "``np.fix`` is pending deprecation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:78
msgid ""
"The ``numpy.fix`` function will be deprecated in a future release. It is "
"recommended to use ``numpy.trunc`` instead, as it provides the same "
"functionality of truncating decimal values to their integer parts. Static "
"type checkers might already report a warning for the use of ``numpy.fix``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:83
msgid "(`gh-30168 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/30168>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:86
msgid "in-place modification of ``ndarray.shape`` is pending deprecation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:87
msgid ""
"Setting the ``ndarray.shape`` attribute directly will be deprecated in a "
"future release.  Instead of modifying the shape in place, it is recommended "
"to use the ``numpy.reshape`` function.  Static type checkers might already "
"report a warning for assignments to ``ndarray.shape``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:92
msgid "(`gh-30282 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/30282>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:95
msgid "Deprecation of ``numpy.lib.user_array.container``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:96
msgid ""
"The ``numpy.lib.user_array.container`` class is deprecated and will be "
"removed in a future version."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:99
msgid "(`gh-30284 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/30284>`__)"
