#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:665
msgid "(`gh-28896 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/28896>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:668
msgid "Fix bug in ``matmul`` for non-contiguous out kwarg parameter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:669
msgid ""
"In some cases, if ``out`` was non-contiguous, ``np.matmul`` would cause "
"memory corruption or a c-level assert. This was new to v2.3.0 and fixed in "
"v2.3.1."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:672
msgid "(`gh-29179 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/29179>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:675
msgid "``__array_interface__`` with NULL pointer changed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:676
msgid ""
"The array interface now accepts NULL pointers (NumPy will do its own dummy "
"allocation, though).  Previously, these incorrectly triggered an "
"undocumented scalar path.  In the unlikely event that the scalar path was "
"actually desired, you can (for now) achieve the previous behavior via the "
"correct scalar path by not providing a ``data`` field at all."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:682
msgid "(`gh-29338 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/29338>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:685
msgid "``unique_values`` for complex dtypes may return unsorted data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:686
msgid ""
"np.unique now supports hash‐based duplicate removal for complex dtypes.  "
"This enhancement extends the hash‐table algorithm to all complex types "
"('c'), and their extended precision variants.  The hash‐based method "
"provides faster extraction of unique values but does not guarantee that the "
"result will be sorted."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:695
msgid "Sorting ``kind='heapsort'`` now maps to ``kind='quicksort'``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:696
msgid ""
"It is unlikely that this change will be noticed, but if you do see a change "
"in execution time or unstable argsort order, that is likely the cause. "
"Please let us know if there is a performance regression. Congratulate us if "
"it is improved :)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:704
msgid "``numpy.typing.DTypeLike`` no longer accepts ``None``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:705
msgid ""
"The type alias ``numpy.typing.DTypeLike`` no longer accepts ``None``. "
"Instead of"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:707
msgid "dtype: DTypeLike = None"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:711
msgid "it should now be"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:713
msgid "dtype: DTypeLike | None = None"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:717
msgid "instead."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:719
msgid "(`gh-29739 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/29739>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:721
msgid ""
"The ``npymath`` and ``npyrandom`` libraries now have a ``.lib`` rather than "
"a ``.a`` file extension on win-arm64, for compatibility for building with "
"MSVC and ``setuptools``. Please note that using these static libraries is "
"discouraged and for existing projects using it, it's best to use it with a "
"matching compiler toolchain, which is ``clang-cl`` on Windows on Arm."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/2.4.0-notes.rst:727
msgid "(`gh-29750 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/29750>`__)"
msgstr ""
